WEBVTT

00:04.000 --> 00:05.661
[Helen]
Previously on Siren.

00:05.670 --> 00:07.535
[Ryn] It is time
to make baby.

00:07.540 --> 00:09.496
-Mating season?
-Important.

00:09.500 --> 00:12.287
We found out
why you and the others
aren't getting pregnant.

00:12.290 --> 00:15.168
-There are substances.
-Causmg fertility problems.

00:15.170 --> 00:16.740
[Kyle] We're interested
in the fertility research
you've been doing.

00:16.750 --> 00:18.411
It's important work.

00:18.420 --> 00:20.820
[Maddie] There are cameras
in the houseboat.

00:20.830 --> 00:21.876
[Kyle] There's nothing
that goes on in my lab

00:21.880 --> 00:23.324
I don't know about.

00:23.330 --> 00:24.786
So it's authentic?

00:24.790 --> 00:25.996
Who are you?

00:26.000 --> 00:28.457
I know something
bigger's happening here.

00:28.460 --> 00:30.109
Something with the military
and whatever creature
you guys caught?

00:30.120 --> 00:32.076
That's what I'm really after.

00:32.080 --> 00:34.708
[Ben] This is Ryn,
our other intern.

00:34.710 --> 00:36.029
Why Ben's mother hurt?

00:36.040 --> 00:38.110
She tried to get
some medicine.
It hurt her.

00:38.120 --> 00:39.530
I help Ben.

00:39.540 --> 00:42.418
Stem cells from a deepwater
marine creature?

00:42.420 --> 00:44.411
This new treatment
has re-energlzed me.

00:44.420 --> 00:46.456
I feel better
than I did before.

00:46.460 --> 00:48.746
[Helen] My family
has had a burial plot.

00:48.750 --> 00:51.287
I believe the military
raided that graveyard.

00:51.290 --> 00:54.919
If they analyze those bones,
they could ﬁnd us.

00:54.920 --> 00:56.035
[Xander]
I'm worried about Nicole.

00:56.040 --> 00:57.280
I've been trying to reach her.

00:57.290 --> 00:58.530
There's nothing, just crickets.

00:58.540 --> 00:59.916
I'll find her.

00:59.920 --> 01:01.035
[suspenseful music]

01:01.040 --> 01:02.029
Do I know you?

01:14.540 --> 01:17.532
[suspenseful music]

01:19.790 --> 01:20.996
Chris?

01:22.120 --> 01:24.497
It's me, Ben.

01:24.500 --> 01:26.377
[cartoon playing]

01:26.380 --> 01:27.950
From Bristol Cove.

01:30.420 --> 01:31.910
You've got the wrong guy.

01:31.920 --> 01:33.114
[sighs] No.

01:35.620 --> 01:36.575
All right.

01:36.580 --> 01:37.786
Here.

01:37.790 --> 01:38.950
Look.

01:40.080 --> 01:41.616
That's me.

01:41.620 --> 01:42.917
That's you.

01:43.960 --> 01:45.825
And Xander and Calvin

01:45.830 --> 01:47.161
at The Anchor.

01:48.830 --> 01:50.286
[Kyle] Ben?

01:50.290 --> 01:52.997
You're not authorized
to be in this area.

01:53.000 --> 01:54.911
What the hell is going on?

01:56.210 --> 01:58.201
Ben, you really need to leave.

01:58.210 --> 02:01.111
He says he knows me.

02:01.120 --> 02:03.372
It's okay.
I'll take care of it.

02:05.290 --> 02:06.416
What did you do to him?

02:12.710 --> 02:13.779
Bristol Cove?

02:19.210 --> 02:22.031
I am from Bristol Cove.

02:24.880 --> 02:28.077
[ominous music]

02:29.620 --> 02:32.111
[high-pitched call]

02:45.460 --> 02:46.575
Ryn?

02:47.710 --> 02:48.825
Are you all right?

02:50.380 --> 02:51.574
No baby.

02:54.210 --> 02:55.450
You can feel it?

02:55.460 --> 02:56.449
Yes.

03:04.960 --> 03:07.167
This happens
to humans, too.

03:07.170 --> 03:09.115
It can be hard
for us to get pregnant.

03:10.420 --> 03:11.409
Donna had a baby.

03:12.380 --> 03:13.369
Did you ever have one?

03:13.380 --> 03:15.166
No.

03:15.170 --> 03:17.115
Sister was older.

03:18.250 --> 03:21.242
Maybe when I was
ready for baby,

03:24.120 --> 03:26.202
You try?

03:26.210 --> 03:27.245
To have baby with Ben?

03:29.170 --> 03:30.990
Well, no, not yet.

03:31.000 --> 03:32.069
Why not?

03:32.080 --> 03:33.911
It's complicated.

03:33.920 --> 03:35.490
A big decision.

03:37.120 --> 03:39.031
Ryn, you can't give up.

03:40.460 --> 03:42.075
My aunt tried for many years.

03:42.080 --> 03:43.741
Eventually, it happened.

03:43.750 --> 03:45.160
How?

03:45.170 --> 03:48.662
Something called IVF,
a medical procedure.

03:48.670 --> 03:51.537
They take an egg from you
and fertilize it.

03:51.540 --> 03:55.533
Basically, they make a baby
outside your body with science.

03:55.540 --> 03:58.327
Then they place it
inside you to grow.

04:05.000 --> 04:06.536
[Kyle] After we got you
out of jail,

04:06.540 --> 04:08.201
Chris was in bad shape.

04:08.210 --> 04:09.575
You guys
just let him walk away.

04:09.580 --> 04:11.536
We found him,
brought him here.

04:11.540 --> 04:14.998
His EEG showed
disturbing changes
from that song.

04:15.000 --> 04:18.163
It was devouring
his frontal cortex.

04:21.830 --> 04:22.876
and we've been treating him.

04:23.880 --> 04:25.529
With what?

04:25.540 --> 04:28.612
The recording
that you captured
from the echo chamber.

04:28.620 --> 04:30.247
We've been exposing him
to it consistently

04:30.250 --> 04:31.615
over these past few weeks,

04:31.620 --> 04:33.372
and his recovery
has been remarkable.

04:33.380 --> 04:35.166
I'd like to see
hIS brain scans.

04:37.080 --> 04:38.160
Sure.

04:46.790 --> 04:49.031
The damage
has largely receded.

04:49.040 --> 04:50.109
It's a huge improvement.

04:50.120 --> 04:51.997
Except he can't
remember anything.

04:52.000 --> 04:54.241
We're hopeful
that'll improve over time.

04:56.170 --> 04:58.161
Maddie and I were exposed
to the echo chamber.

04:58.170 --> 04:59.740
We've had no memory loss.

04:59.750 --> 05:01.615
Chris' damage
was much more extensive.

05:01.620 --> 05:02.609
We've given him
many more treatments

05:02.620 --> 05:04.167
at higher intensity.

05:05.500 --> 05:08.071
Ben, it saved his life.

05:09.540 --> 05:12.031
Look, how much longer
you gonna keep him here?

05:12.040 --> 05:15.828
We're not keeping him
anywhere.

05:15.830 --> 05:17.320
He's free to come and go
as he pleases.

05:17.330 --> 05:18.740
He's chosen to stay.

05:18.750 --> 05:21.412
So I-- I can take him
with me right now?

05:21.420 --> 05:23.536
If he wants to go,
yes, of course.

05:23.540 --> 05:27.169
Might be good for him,
help jog his memory.

05:32.040 --> 05:34.417
[Helen] I'm so sorry
we've been put in danger.

05:34.420 --> 05:36.411
[Beth] We've prepared
ourselves for the worst,

05:36.420 --> 05:38.957
as we live in fear
of being discovered.

05:40.210 --> 05:41.871
Persecuted
for being different.

05:43.540 --> 05:46.282
[Helen] So you've created
a safe haven for yourself.

05:46.290 --> 05:47.450
For all of us.

05:47.460 --> 05:49.701
We have a plan in place.

05:49.710 --> 05:52.076
We'd go into hiding
if necessary.

05:52.080 --> 05:54.457
We're well supplied.

05:54.460 --> 05:56.997
Even our medical needs
could be handled from here.

05:57.000 --> 05:59.412
We have our own doctor,
one of us.

06:03.710 --> 06:06.611
Oh, I've been
self-diagnosing
and self-treating

06:06.620 --> 06:07.951
ever since I can remember.

06:11.120 --> 06:13.748
All of our babies
have been born right here.

06:15.290 --> 06:16.279
Even my own.

06:18.290 --> 06:20.167
It's good to know
you're prepared.

06:26.000 --> 06:27.570
What am I looking at?

06:27.580 --> 06:30.492
This is footage
taken the night of
the Klesco Oil attack.

06:30.500 --> 06:31.956
That's over 2,500 feet down.

06:31.960 --> 06:32.995
This isn't real.

06:33.000 --> 06:34.115
I had it authenticated.

06:34.120 --> 06:35.417
So what does that mean?

06:35.420 --> 06:36.990
I don't know.

06:38.250 --> 06:40.161
I can't explain it.
Here.

06:41.540 --> 06:43.201
Looks like there's
something on her face.

06:43.210 --> 06:44.700
Some kind of scales.

06:44.710 --> 06:45.995
It's weird, right?

06:48.210 --> 06:50.701
Ian, what's going on here?

06:50.710 --> 06:52.075
I have a theory.

06:52.080 --> 06:53.911
It's gonna sound crazy.

06:53.920 --> 06:57.117
I think that this girl,
or whatever she is,

06:57.120 --> 06:59.611
works for the military
and spearheaded
the attack on Klesco.

07:01.040 --> 07:02.371
I think
that she's some kind of

07:03.710 --> 07:05.075
government experiment.

07:05.080 --> 07:06.616
Like she's been, uh,

07:08.120 --> 07:09.030
altered or something.

07:09.040 --> 07:10.029
Altered?

07:11.580 --> 07:13.036
Something not natural.

07:15.290 --> 07:16.871
This is all the evidence
you have?

07:16.880 --> 07:17.915
For now.

07:17.920 --> 07:20.161
This isn't proof of anything.

07:21.290 --> 07:23.667
You want to know
what real evidence would be?

07:23.670 --> 07:25.114
Her.

07:35.080 --> 07:38.038
To do Ivy-Eff,
you say we need him?

07:38.040 --> 07:39.667
Just to be a donor.

07:39.670 --> 07:41.035
We'd need doctors, too,

07:41.040 --> 07:42.780
like at the military lab.

07:42.790 --> 07:45.247
It could get complicated
having them involved.

07:48.580 --> 07:49.660
Stop!

07:51.210 --> 07:52.029
He stays.

07:54.120 --> 07:55.200
You go back.

07:55.210 --> 07:56.825
Ryn, I'm not sure--

07:56.830 --> 07:58.036
Now.

08:14.540 --> 08:15.495
[snoring lightly]

08:15.500 --> 08:17.286
[tapping]

08:17.290 --> 08:19.030
Oh.

08:19.040 --> 08:20.780
Hey, did you, uh...
Did you find Nicole?

08:20.790 --> 08:22.530
No.

08:22.540 --> 08:24.030
But I found someone else.

08:27.080 --> 08:28.240
What the hell?

08:28.250 --> 08:30.070
-Chris!
-Hey.

08:31.790 --> 08:32.916
Chris,

08:32.920 --> 08:34.490
this is Xander.

08:36.120 --> 08:37.280
It's nice to meet you.

08:38.330 --> 08:39.456
Go on.

08:41.040 --> 08:44.112
Uh, yeah.

08:44.120 --> 08:46.327
Yeah, it's nice
to meet you, too.

08:48.670 --> 08:49.785
All right, come on.

08:56.580 --> 08:57.660
I'll explain later.

09:04.670 --> 09:06.206
[Chris]
So this is your place?

09:06.210 --> 09:08.826
Yeah. Go ahead.

09:08.830 --> 09:10.240
Check it out.

09:17.540 --> 09:18.871
You think being with us

09:18.880 --> 09:20.029
is gonna help him
get his memory back?

09:20.040 --> 09:21.667
It might.

09:21.670 --> 09:23.240
We don't know.

09:23.250 --> 09:25.320
But you and Maddie listened
to the same underwater noise.

09:25.330 --> 09:26.877
How come your memory
isn't shot?

09:26.880 --> 09:30.202
He had more treatments,
higher intensity.

09:30.210 --> 09:32.075
What if you and Maddie
need those treatments again?

09:32.080 --> 09:33.661
How are you sure
that this isn't

09:33.670 --> 09:34.876
how you two
are gonna end up?

09:34.880 --> 09:37.531
Honestly,
we don't know exactly

09:37.540 --> 09:39.417
what the military
did to him.

09:39.420 --> 09:41.160
There was no sign
of Nicole in there?

09:41.170 --> 09:42.819
No.

09:42.830 --> 09:44.206
You text her again?

09:44.210 --> 09:45.199
Yeah, like, 20 times.

09:48.250 --> 09:49.569
Go.

09:58.040 --> 09:59.450
We, uh...

09:59.460 --> 10:01.530
used to fish together.

10:02.540 --> 10:03.529
Oh, yeah.

10:03.540 --> 10:04.996
Yeah.

10:09.250 --> 10:10.820
Aw, shit.

10:10.830 --> 10:14.379
[ominous music]

10:28.880 --> 10:31.246
This is my dad.

10:32.250 --> 10:33.319
He had a boat.

10:34.380 --> 10:35.369
The North Star.

10:35.380 --> 10:36.779
Looks like a cool guy.

10:37.960 --> 10:39.029
I'd like to meet him.

10:41.210 --> 10:42.245
Yeah.

10:44.000 --> 10:45.240
He died.

10:47.000 --> 10:49.070
I'm... I'm sorry.

10:53.210 --> 10:54.666
When we were, uh,

10:54.670 --> 10:56.206
out on the boat,

10:59.420 --> 11:00.614
we came under attack.

11:02.250 --> 11:07.324
These things
came out of the water.

11:07.330 --> 11:08.490
It was all around us.

11:09.500 --> 11:10.615
[spear clanks]

11:12.540 --> 11:13.700
[grunts]

11:16.170 --> 11:18.070
[Donna shrieks]

11:20.080 --> 11:24.198
[singing Siren song]

11:24.210 --> 11:25.825
[knock on door]

11:30.880 --> 11:32.245
Hey.

11:32.250 --> 11:34.206
I got here
as fast as I could.

11:36.080 --> 11:37.069
How's he doing?

11:37.080 --> 11:38.069
He's not great.

11:41.170 --> 11:41.989
Hey.

11:42.000 --> 11:43.536
[Xander] Chris?

11:45.120 --> 11:47.076
This is Calvin.

11:47.080 --> 11:48.911
[Calvin] Hey, man,
I know you don't remember me,

11:48.920 --> 11:51.821
but I, uh...
I brought you some stuff.

11:51.830 --> 11:54.287
I know the memory's
been foggy, so

11:54.290 --> 11:56.326
I thought that
these things could help.

11:58.540 --> 12:00.167
Cap'n Crunch? Really?

12:00.170 --> 12:03.116
Yeah. They say taste and smell
triggers the memory.

12:04.120 --> 12:05.496
You loved this stuff, hmm?

12:05.500 --> 12:07.115
[cell phone chimes]

12:07.120 --> 12:09.202
Got you your favorite candy,
some snacks.

12:09.210 --> 12:11.201
You used to love all this.

12:11.210 --> 12:11.995
All your favorites.

12:13.000 --> 12:15.412
Check this out.

12:15.420 --> 12:16.910
What is this?

12:16.920 --> 12:18.569
It's your favorite beer.

12:20.830 --> 12:22.491
[chimes]

12:22.500 --> 12:25.708
Hey, I gotta go
see Maddie and Ryn.

12:25.710 --> 12:28.201
Right. Um, we're
gonna take Chris
to The Anchor.

12:28.210 --> 12:30.201
Hopefully,
it'll jog his memory.

12:30.210 --> 12:32.110
We got this.

12:32.120 --> 12:33.075
Okay.

12:33.080 --> 12:34.707
Keep me posted,
all right?

12:34.710 --> 12:36.200
-Let me know how he's doing.
-All right.

12:36.210 --> 12:37.780
It's good
to see you, man.

12:39.080 --> 12:40.786
We can't do this
with the military.

12:40.790 --> 12:42.530
Even if it was successful,

12:42.540 --> 12:44.781
they'd never let us transfer
the embryo back to Ryn.

12:44.790 --> 12:46.166
They'd want to control it.

12:46.170 --> 12:47.740
But is mine.

12:47.750 --> 12:49.706
They would grow the baby
in the lab without you.

12:51.000 --> 12:53.821
Maybe Nicole?
She can help?

12:53.830 --> 12:55.070
I don't know
where Nicole is.

12:55.080 --> 12:56.786
There's no one
you trust there?

12:56.790 --> 12:58.417
No, especially now.

12:58.420 --> 12:59.819
What do you mean?

12:59.830 --> 13:02.412
When I went back there,

13:02.420 --> 13:03.535
I saw some things.

13:06.080 --> 13:07.286
They did it.

13:08.290 --> 13:09.370
The graveyard.

13:09.380 --> 13:11.610
As we suspected.

13:14.460 --> 13:17.031
We'll do it without them
with our own doctors.

13:17.040 --> 13:20.077
We can't just take Ryn
to a fertility clinic.

13:20.080 --> 13:21.707
Beth. Her people.

13:21.710 --> 13:22.995
They have
their own doctors.

13:23.000 --> 13:24.661
Hi, it's Helen.

13:24.670 --> 13:26.160
A question.

13:26.170 --> 13:28.491
Can you tell me more
about the doctors
at the ranch?

13:28.500 --> 13:29.876
Ryn.

13:31.040 --> 13:33.873
I'm so sorry
about your sister.

13:35.040 --> 13:37.702
That is not my sister.

13:38.710 --> 13:39.699
Only her bones.

13:40.920 --> 13:41.989
Not...

13:43.830 --> 13:45.286
-her.
-Yeah.

13:47.920 --> 13:49.376
They took Chris, too.

13:49.380 --> 13:50.824
What?

13:50.830 --> 13:52.661
They grabbed him
before he went back to Iowa.

13:52.670 --> 13:54.376
They said
he was losing it.

13:54.380 --> 13:55.665
They've been treating him

13:55.670 --> 13:57.376
with the recording
we took down there.

13:57.380 --> 13:58.495
How is he doing?

13:58.500 --> 13:59.489
Not great.

14:01.040 --> 14:03.076
It's pretty much wiped
his memory.

14:03.080 --> 14:04.377
-[Maddie] Ben!
-I know.

14:04.380 --> 14:05.745
I know.

14:05.750 --> 14:07.536
We gotta make it
clear to them

14:07.540 --> 14:09.747
that they're
not in control of us.

14:09.750 --> 14:11.286
I pulled out the cameras,
all of them.

14:11.290 --> 14:12.530
Good.

14:12.540 --> 14:14.076
Okay.

14:14.080 --> 14:16.878
I'll let you know.

14:16.880 --> 14:18.245
What did she say?

14:18.250 --> 14:21.162
They could implant
the fertilized egg.

14:21.170 --> 14:24.207
But extracting the egg,
then fertilizing the egg,

14:24.210 --> 14:27.373
requires special equipment
and expertise they don't have.

14:27.380 --> 14:31.749
Okay, so let's have
the military do that part,

14:31.750 --> 14:34.878
then we'll get Beth's doctors
to transfer it to Ryn.

14:34.880 --> 14:38.202
You just said the military
isn't gonna hand
that embryo over.

14:38.210 --> 14:39.074
[Ben] They won't.

14:40.540 --> 14:41.780
We'd have to take it.

14:43.080 --> 14:45.378
[keyboard clicking]

14:47.920 --> 14:49.239
Ted, I thought
you left already.

14:49.250 --> 14:50.990
You're still here.

14:51.000 --> 14:53.377
Hey. Yeah.
Uh, just heading out.

14:53.380 --> 14:54.745
Back for dinner?

14:54.750 --> 14:56.911
Oh, well,
I'll do my best, sweetie.

14:59.920 --> 15:01.569
You okay?

15:01.580 --> 15:03.457
You touched my leg.

15:04.830 --> 15:05.876
Ted, I felt it.

15:08.250 --> 15:09.535
[gaSPSI

15:09.540 --> 15:10.780
Here?

15:10.790 --> 15:12.075
I definitely feel something.

15:25.580 --> 15:26.990
What do you think?
Get him some food?

15:27.000 --> 15:28.206
Yeah.
I think Janine's working.

15:28.210 --> 15:29.450
Maybe seeing her
will help.

15:29.460 --> 15:31.075
[Calvin] Yeah.

15:31.080 --> 15:34.572
[Siren song echoing]

15:49.620 --> 15:51.030
[Xander, distant sounding]
Chris?

15:54.540 --> 15:55.871
[echoing] Chris!

15:57.670 --> 15:58.876
Chris?

16:00.040 --> 16:01.246
You all right, man?

16:02.540 --> 16:03.996
Yeah.

16:06.040 --> 16:07.075
Yeah.

16:12.080 --> 16:13.991
[ominous music]

16:17.500 --> 16:19.456
The equipment will be
set up right away,

16:19.460 --> 16:21.917
then our doctors
can retrieve the eggs from Ryn.

16:24.040 --> 16:26.531
And as for the male sample?

16:27.880 --> 16:29.029
We'll have that.

16:31.000 --> 16:32.877
Look, at this point,
we should probably

16:32.880 --> 16:34.825
all put our cards on the table,
don't you think?

16:34.830 --> 16:36.286
Is this when you tell us

16:36.290 --> 16:38.531
about the cameras
you hid in my house?

16:38.540 --> 16:41.282
It's my job
to gather information
about these creatures,

16:41.290 --> 16:44.168
how they behave,
if they pose a threat.

16:44.170 --> 16:45.660
You crossed a line.

16:45.670 --> 16:48.036
But sometimes that's the cost
of gaining knowledge.

16:49.170 --> 16:50.910
How's Chris doing?

16:50.920 --> 16:53.662
Getting out of here
has been good for him.

16:53.670 --> 16:56.036
So that recording
that you got down there

16:56.040 --> 16:58.668
might just be the treatment
that he needed after all.

16:58.670 --> 17:00.820
You see?

17:00.830 --> 17:03.572
Good things happen
when we collaborate.

17:08.000 --> 17:09.490
Our doctor will be prepared

17:09.500 --> 17:11.616
as soon
as we receive the embryo.

17:11.620 --> 17:12.996
-Good.
-And, Helen,

17:13.000 --> 17:14.786
this is what
